I’ve been crackin’ nuts since 1906. 🥜 I’ll make my return to the scene of the crime (Kneegate) Saturday, December 10th at 2pm at the @segerstromarts Center in Costa Mesa, CA. Get tickets via my story or bio. Bring my book and I’ll sign it at the stage door after the show. 💕 Can’t wait to get back on that horse, even if it is a bucking bronco.

I’m performing “The Nutcracker” this Saturday on the same stage I ruptured my patellar tendon less than a year ago, where I laid on the ground, face down, with my head in my hands, in shock and wishing to disappear, while the orchestra petered out to silence before the curtain was drawn. Being here again, I’m nervous, but not for the quality of my performance, but for the safety of my body. It’s a different dancer-life now. It’s one that I have fought for and for which I am grateful. This video is very special to me. It shows the beauty of not the art, the dance, or the work, but of the spirit of our community of artists. The company’s applause at the end of the video is the sound of empathy and I will cherish it forever. 
And thank you, @isabellaboylston, for being there with me through it all.

One of my coaches said that this year’s performance of “The Nutcracker” was a cosmic redo, which I thought was chic. Being able to finish the performance this year, after having to be pushed offstage in a wheelchair last year, was overwhelming in the best way. I’m full of gratitude and love for what I do and the people I do it with. I couldn’t do it without @isabellaboylston by my side, and all of the @abtofficial dancers and staff. And thank you to the @segerstromarts Center and the INCREDIBLE and GENEROUS California audiences. Your energy is what keeps us going. ⚡️
And with that, I’m gonna shut the hell up about Kneegate for a while. 🙊😘

A Very California Nutcracker 🌴🥜
This performance marked my last under Artistic Director Kevin McKenzie, who has been my boss, mentor, coach, and therapist for the past 10 years. Thank you for the kindness, opportunity, and wisdom you so freely give. 🙏

I walked down aisle 6 of the Gristedes in midtown and this little old lady asked me if I could reach the canned fava beans, which were on the top shelf. I said, “No, but YOU can.” And I grabbed her by the waist, right over her muumuu, and threw her up to the top shelf, where the fava beans teetered precariously under her house slippers that she wore as shoes. She yelled from her great heights, “Thank you, young man!” 🫘

Tyra Banks asked me for directions once. She tapped me on my (left) shoulder and asked, “Which way to the nearest Gristedes. I said, “Just go two blocks east (left) and you can’t miss it.” She smiled, well, smized really, and said, “You’re a doll. I’ve been dying to get something to munch on before my fitting for the Victoria’s Secret fashion show.” I was “straight” at the time and didn’t know what that was, so I said, “What’s that? Sounds gay.” And Tyra Banks said, “Oh, darling, it is! It’s the gayest thing since the Thunderpuss remix of ‘It’s Not Right. But It’s OK!’” And we lauuuuuughed. Then she (left).

A woman I met at the stage door told me a story about how she was diagnosed with cancer at the same time that I injured my knee a year ago. She told me that this was the first ballet she was seeing cancer free. It made me feel so many things. 🥹💕

I miss my mother. Getting to share her story, our story, is one of my proudest moments. I often wonder what she would have thought about it. I hope she would have felt the love in every word. She deserved the love of the whole world. I, to this day, believe she should have been an actress, a pop star, a poet laureate, whatever. She was pure charisma. 
She died on this day, seven years ago. I get sad when I least expect it, like an ambush.
Give your mother a call today, or whomever really. A friend, a lover, a family member. Give them your love.

My first performance in ABT’S Summer Season in four years happens TOMORROW. A pandemic and a shartbreath of a knee injury kept me off this stage for a spell, but I’ve been working my ass off to get back to fighting shape, along with the help of my surgeon, physical therapists, coaches, and loved ones, of course. See you tomorrow for a 2pm performance of “Giselle” with me and @cassandratrenary ❤️ come see us at the stage door after for pics and hellos 🕺✨

THANK YOU for the love we felt from the audience yesterday. 🙏❤️ I felt grateful and present during my first show back on the Met stage with ABT. Thank you @cassandratrenary for being so generous out there with me. Love you, friend! When I was dancing with the opera earlier this year, the dancers would get in a circle and hold hands before the show. The dance captain would lead what felt essentially like a prayer to the gods of art and theater and something they said each time was, “Nothing to prove, everything to share.” J’obsessed. Ok, now onto Swan Lake! See you Wednesday at 7:30pm. Get tickets via link in bio. Bring my book to the stage door. I’ll sign it and say hey girl hey. ❤️

Excited to announce that my play #DEADCENTER will be premiering at @theatreaspenco's New Works Festival, Solo Flights from 9/7 to 9/14! 🎭 Join me in Aspen for an unforgettable experience. Get your tickets now at TheatreAspen.org. See you there! #TheatreAspen #SoloFlights
-
Play description: James Whiteside is a thrilling multifaceted artist whose personal story is as unique as his artistic virtuosity as one of the world’s greatest ballet dancers. James uses dance, song, and high camp to process the death of his complicated and beloved mother, and the near death of his dance career after a brutal knee injury. He reminds us all that there is life after change and the only way through… is through. Join us for the most fun funeral you’ll ever attend. ⚰️🥳
-
The play is based on my book, CENTER CENTER. If you haven’t read it yet, get it at the link in my bio.

🩰🍽️ #BallerinoDiner - Nancy’s Corn Casserole 🌽
-
This is one of the last recipes that my mom taught me. It’s an absolute banger and people lose their minds over it. Try it, take a pic, and tag me and #BallerinoDiner ❤️
-
🩰 preheat oven to 350°
🩰 grease casserole dish or baking cups
🩰 mix one box jiffy cornbread, one can creamed corn, one can kernel corn, 2 eggs, 1/4c sugar, 1 stick butter, and 1c sour cream in mixing bowl
🩰 transfer batter to greased dish or baking cups
🩰 bake for 1 hour
🩰 remove, cool for 3-5mins, enjoy! Goes great with Nancy’s chili
-
🎥 @scottienorton

#TheBallerinoDiner - Chicken Pot Pie 🥧 If you make it, take a pic and tag me 💕
-
Ingredients:
Top & bottom refrigerated pie crusts
4 c. cooked, shredded rotisserie chicken
6 tbsp. Unsalted butter
⅓ c. chopped onion
1 c. thinly sliced carrots
½ c. sliced celery
8 oz. cremini mushrooms, destemmed and sliced
3 cloves minced garlic
⅓ c. all purpose flour
2 c. chicken stock (plus more for base thinning, if neccessary)
½ c. heavy cream
2 tsp. fine salt
¼ tsp. black pepper
¼ tsp. celery seed
1 c. frozen peas
1 egg, beaten (for crush wash)
¼ c. fresh chopped parsley (optional)

Directions:
Preheat oven to 425 degrees F
In dutch oven, saute onions in butter over medium heat
Add carrots & celery, saute around 8 mins
Add mushrooms & garlic, saute 5 more mins
Add flour slowly & stir constantly, 2 mins
Add chicken stock, heavy cream, simmer 1 min until thick like gravy
Add salt, pepper, celery seed (can be seasoned to taste)
Add chicken, stir, remove from heat
Roll bottom crust into pie plate
Fill with chicken mixture
Cover with remaining pie crust and seal edges with fingers
Press edges closed with fork
Brush beaten egg on top
Make venting slits with knife
Lightly season top with coarse salt and freshly ground pepper
Bake at 425 degrees F for 30-45 mins
Remove, let stand for 5-10 mins before serving
Garnish with parsley and enjoy
🥧

Meet Lovers James and Augie, 💞
 
James Whiteside, a prominent American ballet dancer and choreographer, met Augie Schott, a promising real estate developer,at a volleyball court in Fire Island Pines. They spend their weekends at The Maker Hotel to unwind and renew. Their love is noted for its unspoken commitment and inseparable bond that is all about unity and serendipity.
 
Follow along for more love stories from the #Makerlovers and experience Lover Eau de Parfum @sephora.
